properties.name: Japan Hill/Da Mee Rak
properties.description: Posted by Sjobeck7225 w oakland park blvd, 33319Whether it is Japanese & Korean does not matter as much as it does matter that the food is excellent. This was our second time there (Jack, Eliza, Jess, Allie, Jennifer, Jason) after having been a few years back (Paul, Susan, Nat, Marta, Jess, Jennifer, Jason)(pregnant with Allie) and we had mostly sushi/sashimi which was great. Tonight I had very spicy hot octopus, Jennifer had lots of scallops, Jack had some sort of soup, Elizabeth had some sort of sliced beef, the girls had ebi shumai, which they really liked, so we ordered a second for them. Good dinner after a day (trying to) snorkeling Grecian Rocks off Key Largo.

properties.name: best Italian meal
properties.description: Posted by Sjobeck Got to be one of the best if not the singular best Italian I have ever had. These guys really are from Italy, speak Italian, serve Italian, there are Italians eating there, it was superb. Ravoli was superb, service fast, Tiramisu was fabulous, everything, I dont think you can make a mistake ordering anything here, even if it is is not what you were expecting it will most likely be perfect in some othe way you were not expecting.

properties.name: best seafood in Portland as well as the chocolate bag
properties.description: Posted by Sjobeck401 Southwest 12th Avenue, Portland, OR, 97205They pour chocolate into a mold of a bag then let it freeze, then tear it apart before they serve it, then fill it with two kinds of mousse, and tons of berries, and berry sauce, it is our family\'s favorite desert in town. Tim Lohse takes us all here whenever he is in town visiting, which is tremendously enjoyable for all. Thank you, Tim. Generally one of the best places in the state. Note the trough that runs down the front of the bar, which is obviously no longer in use, that gentlemen used to be able to use to save themselves a trip to the john, when drinking here in the goold ole days.
